<span class="name"><a name="99823"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#1:&nbsp;<font color=black><b>Game Idea ... Is This Feasible?</b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Montril</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=99823#99823"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Thu Mar 24, 2005 3:22 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">As I get older (don't ask  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> ) I am finding I have less patients with the MMORPG crowd. I have grouped with many great people but I am finding I don't want to weed through the immature to find them. Now when I play WOW (game I am currently playing) I solo or play with my 3 RL friends. 
<br />

<br />
Do you think someone will ever make a game that
<br />

<br />
1. A world that will handle between 6-10 people
<br />
2. The game would be open ended like the MMORPG's
<br />
3. No monthly fees because the server would be your own.
<br />
4. The world would evolve through triggers (time/events/level of players) so the content would adjust. Example: There would be lots of early quests, kill the pirate who is stopping supplies from reaching the dock. If you do the quest early and kill him, his superior (who is higher level) later on would come and see what happened to him and lay waste to the town. If you miss the quest later on when you get to town the pirate would have gained levels would now control the town. 
<br />
5. Crafting would be available.
<br />
6. Once a quest was done there might be an effect but the pirate above would be dead.
<br />
7. Buying/making/capturing tower/castle for yourself (plus furnishing it)
<br />

<br />
Would a game like be possible?
<br />
1. Would there be a big enough market for this game?
<br />
2. Would companies give up the monthly fees?
<br />
3. Is the scope of something like this just too big?
<br />

<br />
A game like Morrowind has a base for this but it needs so much more. There are a couple of worlds in Neverwinters Nights but again its not there.
<br />

<br />
Am I just dreaming
<br />

<br />
TL</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
